Nicely hopped beer with a solid backbone of sweetness that balances the high abv well. On the front, there is a nice hint of sour.

I had this on cask at the brewery. Phenomenal beer. Super smooth roasty stout that goes down too easily. Compared to the normal kegged version, the casked option is untouchable. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is definitely my favorite tripel. On the nose, the bourbon is clear. The taste is phenomenal with a nice sour finish. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Absolutely the best tripel I've ever had. Normally they are way too sweet for my liking but these guys have nailed it, great taste with a nice bite. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This is a phenomenal dubbel. With a higher abv than the average dubbel, these monks have found a beautiful way to marry full taste and high abv without a pungent alcohol taste. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A very good beer for the price. Bought this at a hole in the wall In the Netherlands.   Not bad for the price, but I wouldn't travel to Europe just to have it. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Excellent seasonal beer. This is, by far, my favorite pumpkin beer, I just wish it were easier to get.

Excellent beer. This is a very well balanced double I.P.A. That mixes a high 10% abv with a nice clean finish.

This is just hops. I think lagunitas just soaked a few bucketfuls of hops in water. There is not much flavor other than hops.

Should be labeled as "a very black I.P.A."  The taste is sweet with a nice, hoppy finish.

Really good imperial ipa but quite light considering. Good all-round ipa.  Luckily it's easy to find.
